{
  "texts": [
    "This would decrease the cost and required effort to deploy foundation models for an even wider range of downstream tasks.",
    "Moreover, in-context learning allows to improve model performance by crafting adequate prompts without parameter updates (frequently referred to as prompt engineering).",
    "The property of emergent capabilities also raises concerns.",
    "Emergence implies a substantial uncertainty over the capabilities, flaws, and limitations of foundational models, making it hard to understand, explain, and predict their behavior and potential failure modes (Bommasani et al. 2021).",
    "This is illustrated by the extent to which slightly altered prompts may cause considerably different outcomes; that is, small changes to the model input can cause a large change in its qualitative behavior."
  ]
}